title: non-small cell lung cancer patient 10111N
source_name_ch1: fresh frozen lung tissues from non-small cell lung cancer patients
characteristics_ch1.10: death due to lung cancer (all years): Dead
extract_protocol_ch1: One microgram of total RNA  was extracted for each sample using TRIzol following the manufacturer’s protocol (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Waltham, MA). Isolated total RNA was quantified using a NanoDrop 1000 (NanoDrop Products, Wilmington, DE). RNA integrity was determined using an Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: One microgram of total RNA was labeled for each sample according to Affymetrix protocols (GeneChip Expression Analysis Technical Manual).
hyb_protocol: Hybridization cocktails were prepared, including each fragmented target, and probe array controls. They were then hybridized to Affymetrix HG-U133 2.0 plus arrays during a 16-hour incubation (GeneChip Expression Analysis Technical Manual).
scan_protocol: Once the probe arrays were hybridized, washed, and stained, they were scanned using a GeneChip Scanner 3000 for High-Resolution Scanning (GeneChip Expression Analysis Technical Manual).
description: Gene expression data from fresh frozen lung tissues
data_processing: The data were analyzed by using Affymetrix Gene Chip Operating Software using default settings.

extract_protocol_ch1: One microgram of total RNA  was extracted for each sample using TRIzol following the manufacturer’s protocol (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Waltham, MA). Isolated total RNA was quantified using a NanoDrop 1000 (NanoDrop Products, Wilmington, DE). RNA integrity was determined using an Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: One microgram of total RNA was labeled for each sample according to Affymetrix protocols (GeneChip Expression Analysis Technical Manual).
hyb_protocol: Hybridization cocktails were prepared, including each fragmented target, and probe array controls. They were then hybridized to Affymetrix HG-U133 2.0 plus arrays during a 16-hour incubation (GeneChip Expression Analysis Technical Manual).
scan_protocol: Once the probe arrays were hybridized, washed, and stained, they were scanned using a GeneChip Scanner 3000 for High-Resolution Scanning (GeneChip Expression Analysis Technical Manual).
description: Gene expression data from fresh frozen lung tissues
data_processing: The data were analyzed by using Affymetrix Gene Chip Operating Software using default settings.
